<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1881-12-02T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1881-12-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="269" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d269">
                    <head>No. 265.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Blaine</persName>
                            to Mr. <persName type="to">Morton</persName></hi>.</head>
                    <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1881-12-02"><hi rend="italic">December</hi> 2,
                            1881</date>.</dateline></opener>
                    <p>Ascertain promptly, and advise by telegraph to-morrow, whether, and at what
                        time we may expect revocation of edict prohibiting importation of American
                        pork. Important.</p>
                    <closer><signed>BLAINE.</signed></closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>